    {
      "id": "p002",
      "index": 2,
      "source": "For a chosen tile size, more and more SMEM can be used to increase the stage count and hide more latency. For a given pipeline depth N, if one stage is actively performing MMA, up to N-1 stages’ A and B buffers can be in-flight. Another way to look at it is that the latency for a given load stage can still be fully hidden up to (N-1)\\*M where M is the time for a single stage to perform MMA, so the latency hiding ability strictly increases for a fixed tile size with increasing stage count.",
      "source_html": null,
      "element_type": "p",
      "inline_elements": [],
      "parent_block_id": "b0149",
      "parent_block_index": 149,
      "parent_block_type": "p",
      "parent_block_markdown": "For a chosen tile size, more and more SMEM can be used to increase the stage count and hide more latency. For a given pipeline depth N, if one stage is actively performing MMA, up to N-1 stages’ A and B buffers can be in-flight. Another way to look at it is that the latency for a given load stage can still be fully hidden up to (N-1)\\*M where M is the time for a single stage to perform MMA, so the latency hiding ability strictly increases for a fixed tile size with increasing stage count.",
      "parent_block_plain_text": "For a chosen tile size, more and more SMEM can be used to increase the stage count and hide more latency. For a given pipeline depth N, if one stage is actively performing MMA, up to N-1 stages’ A and B buffers can be in-flight. Another way to look at it is that the latency for a given load stage can still be fully hidden up to (N-1)\\*M where M is the time for a single stage to perform MMA, so the latency hiding ability strictly increases for a fixed tile size with increasing stage count.",
      "parent_source_html": null,
      "parent_inline_elements": [],
      "segment_start": 0,
      "segment_end": 493,
      "expected_tokens": [],
      "format_recovery_status": "not_applicable",
      "format_errors": [],
      "is_heading": false,
      "heading_level": null,
